Open Redirect #  Often a bug that brings impact when chained.
Using &ldquo;https:&rdquo; to bypass &ldquo;//&rdquo; blacklisted keyword
https:google.com Using &ldquo;//&rdquo; to bypass &ldquo;http&rdquo; blacklisted keyword
//google.com Using /\/ to bypass // blacklisted keyword
\/\/google.com/ /\/google.com/ Using &ldquo;/&quot; to bypass:
/\google.com Using &ldquo;%E3%80%82&rdquo; to bypass &ldquo;.&rdquo; blacklisted character
//google%E3%80%82com Using null byte &ldquo;%00&rdquo; to bypass blacklist filter
//google%00.com Using parameter pollution
?next=whitelisted.com&amp;next=google.com Using &ldquo;@&rdquo; character, browser will redirect to anything after the &ldquo;@&rdquo;
